<html>

<body>
   <h1>Java to Javascript Converter</h1>

   <div id="intro">
      Welcome to the free online Java to JS converter.
      <br/>
      Java code is converted into readable Javascript code
      using the StrataCode Java to JS converter. Main limitations:
      <ul>
         <li>Java 1.8 syntax with a subset of Java 1.6 utility libraries, some implemented by hand in
          javasys.js and some converted from the Apache utils with minor edits in jvsys.js.
         <li>All Number types in Java represented as the one JS number type.
      </ul>
   </div>

   <div id="mainForm">
       Enter Java Code for one class<br/>
       <textarea id="inputTextarea" rows="40" cols="80" changeEvent="=: inputSrcText = value"
                 value="=: inputSrcText = value"/>
       <!-- <input id="inputTextarea" changeEvent="=: inputSrcText = value"/> -->

       <br/>
       <input id="doCvtButton" value="Convert to JS" type="button" clickEvent="=: doConvert(0)"/>

      <br/>
      <div id="errorsView"><%= inputErrors %></div>

      <br/>
      JS dependencies:
      <div id="jsFilesView" repeat=":= jsFiles" repeatVarName="jsFile">
         <a href=":= jsFilePrefix + jsFile"><%= jsFile %></a>
      </div>
      <p/>
      JS code for this class:<br/>
      <pre id="resultView"><%= resultSrcText %></pre>
   </div>

</body>

</html>
